HEADWORD: madonna lily
<hw>madonna lily</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A lily
(<spn>Lilium candidum</spn>) of the Eastern Mediterranean and Balkans
with broad funnel-shaped white flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> white lily, Annunciation lily, Lent lily,
<spn>Lilium candidum</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
